<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-06-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="287" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Campbell</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 33.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                                </placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-06-01"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 1, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Proceed with as much despatch as possible to the residence of President
                            Juarez of Mexico, and enter upon your mission. Earnestly urge clemency
                            to Maximilian, and other prisoners of war, if necessary.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Lewis D. Campbell,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c., New Orleans.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>